<CDLItem itemNbr="32-12-03" id="X-BOEING:FTID:81205.787.DDG.CU.CDL.3-32-12-03.1.3-32-12-03">
<Title>Main Landing Gear Strut Door</Title>
<DispatchCondition>
<DispatchConditionRemarks>
<Para>One may be missing provided gear remains extended for 10 minutes after takeoff and the takeoff performance adjustment is applied. Main landing gear strut door may not be missing in combination with main landing gear drag brace door or main landing gear trunnion door. </Para>
<Note>
<Para>Main landing gear lower strut door(s) will also be missing. Additional performance decrements for lower strut doors are not required.</Para>
</Note>
<Para>When the shock strut door is removed, the bolts attaching the strut door to the strut must remain on the shock strut.</Para>
<Para>Limit speed to 270 KIAS / 0.73 Mach.</Para>
<Para>On the MISC SYSTEM CTRLS (MSC) maintenance page, set the Overspeed Warning switch to GEAR DOWN.</Para>
<Para>Procedure:
Do not retract landing gear for 10 minutes after takeoff. In the event of an engine failure after V1, retract the landing gear until a minimum of 1,500 feet above airport elevation and terrain clearance is assured. While maintaining terrain clearance, extend the gear for the balance of the 10 minutes.</Para>
<Para>Reduce performance limited weights by:</Para>
